                     <div class="accordion-item">
                        <a>I am going to work in India, What is the best course option for me?</a>
                        <div class="content">
                           <p>Yaaaay, it's best opportunity to learn Hindi in the Hindi speaking environment itself. If you are coming for short span of time (or just travelling to India for few months), then go for <b>Survival Hindi Course of 14 days</b> and if you are coming for larger amount of work or project of 2-3 years, best course to choose is <b>Spoken Hindi Course of 3 months</b>. Survival Course contains only introductory and basic (Grammar + Vocabulary), but Spoken Course contains (Full Grammar + All Important Vocabulary).</p>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                     <div class="accordion-item">
                        <a>Why should I hire you as my Hindi trainer?</a>
                        <div class="content">
                           <p>Most important things which I offer is my scientific learning of Hindi Language, be it <b>Morphology, Phonetics, Semantics and/or part of Pragmatics </b>. You prepare a very strong fundamental base through mathematical understanding of the Hindi language. Apart from being a native speaker, I am researcher of Hindi Linguistics, so <b>my way of explanation will seem very logical to you at every part of the course</b>.</p>
                        </div>
                     </div>
                     <div class="accordion-item">
                        <a>What do you cover in your Hindi Classes?</a>
                        <div class="content">
                           <p>Every Hindi class starts with discussion of 15-20 minutes (discussion of assignments, situation etc. in Hindi). <b>No books are followed for any of my lecture </b> - all the content which I teach, you have to just make notes. Whenever you will be ready with your fundamentals, you will be provided selectively with :- <b>
                              (1) Printed Notes (2)Vocabulary Cards (3)Culture Cards (4)Collocated Object Cards (5)Assignments (6) Essay Notes (7)Puzzle & Box Games (8)Selected Short Films & Podcasts (9)Speaking Sessions (10)Quick-Expressions Card </b>
